CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 22, 1955, pg. 11, reads: "Sweet Sixteen - Soaring with the stars on the magic sixteenth birthday, was Bootsie Bray, center, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. LuGene Bray, of Iowa Street. Some eighty or more young set members came to the gay party which celebrated the happy event.  Left to right: Buddie and Toni Bray, Kay Stokes, Marva Jo Hord, Gay Cyrus, and on the far right, Carol Jones. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of young men, and young women, including Marva Jo Hord wearing striped dress on left, LouJeanne "Boostie" Bray wearing corsage and holding wrapped gifts on her sixteen birthday, Kay Stokes wearing dark blouse and knotted necklace, and Gay Cyrus on right, posed in Bray home on Iowa Street
